<td align="left" valign="top">
<p><br>Dear {!Contact.Name},<br><br></p>
			<p>We have made changes to improve how passwords work on our NCS booking website. <BR><BR><B>Parents/Guardians and young people will now have separate passwords.</B> You will have an individual password to access your online NCS account, and so will your parent or guardian.</P>
<P>Plus, you will now be able to set up your own password for the booking website so that it will be easier to remember.</P>
<P>These changes will take place on <B>Tuesday 24 February 2015</B>.</P>
<P>We have emailed your parent or guardian separate instructions for setting up their parent/guardian password.</P>

<B>If you are a parent or guardian receiving this email, please pass this on to your child and call us on 0203 542 2400.</B>

<P><HR></P><P><B>Here are the instructions for you to set up your young person password:</B></P>
<P>
<B>1.</B> Go to <a href="http://bookings.ncsthechallenge.org" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(235, 0, 139);" ><B>our booking website</B></A> and click on 'Login'<BR>
<B>2.</B> Click on the blue 'Forgotten password?' link that appears below<BR>
<B>3.</B> Enter <B>your</B> email address and press 'Recover login'<BR><BR>It is important that you enter your own email address, and not your parent or guardian's, as this process will set up the young person password.</P>
<P>Once you have completed these steps, <B>you will receive an email asking you to log in and set up your young person password.</B><BR><HR></P>

<p>If you have any difficulty, or have any questions about this, please call us on 0203 542 2400 or email us at contact@ncsthechallenge.org<p>

<p>Yours sincerely,</P>

<p style="margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px;"><img alt="Tanya Dunne" border="0" height="61" src="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/CCT/Tanya%20Dunne.png?height=30&amp;width=122" width="122"></p>
Tanya Dunne<BR>
Head of Customer Services - The Challenge


